# TitanClip: AI Company Orchestration Platform

> [!NOTE]
> High-velocity autonomous agent orchestration governed by enterprise-grade security and Runtime Agentic IAM. Built on Paperclip.

## Overview
TitanClip is an enterprise-ready digital workforce management platform. It allows organizations to deploy teams of autonomous AI agents that collaborate, delegate, and execute tasks within a governed command structure. It features a robust security layer to prevent "rogue" agent behavior through fail-safe controls and ironclad guardrails.

## Core Features
- **Runtime Agentic IAM:** Granular identity and access management for AI agents.
- **Credential Vault:** AES-256-GCM encrypted secrets management for agent tool access.
- **Heartbeat Orchestration:** Real-time monitoring and synchronization of autonomous actions.
- **Agent Analytics:** Performance tracking, cost attribution, and velocity forecasting.
- **Multi-Adapter Support:** Native integration with 9+ LLM providers.
- **Skill System:** Extensible agent capabilities via a dedicated Skill SDK.

## Technical Stack
- **Runtime:** Electron 33 (Desktop Application)
- **Frontend:** React 19, Vite 6, Tailwind CSS 4 (OKLCH theming)
- **Backend:** Express.js with embedded PostgreSQL
- **ORM:** Drizzle ORM
- **Auth:** better-auth
- **Architecture:** Monorepo using `pnpm` workspaces

## Key Directories
- `/packages`: Shared logic, DB schemas (@titanclip/db), and LLM adapters.
- `/server`: Core orchestration logic, heartbeat service, and vault management.
- `/ui`: React-based dashboard, agent chat interface, and command center.
- `/skills`: Pre-configured agent capabilities and tools.

## Integration & Development
TitanClip uses a plugin-based architecture. Developers can extend agent capabilities using the `@titanclip/plugin-sdk`. It supports streaming UI components and tool cards directly within the agent chat interface.

## Target Use Cases
- Enterprise process automation
- Secure multi-agent collaboration
- Governed AI workforce deployment
- Automated DevSecOps and vulnerability scanning

